    Go find the other spirits. #line:0e334e8 
<<else>>
    <<card ritratto_pisano>>
    I am Nicola Pisano, a medieval sculptor. #line:0126c77
    It was the year 1260 when I first came here. #line:03e7256 
    <<card pisano>>
    I chose this marble for the Baptistery of Pisa. #line:0668c76 
    But before making art... you need to extract the marble! #line:088bd28 
    Let me explain how it has been done through the centuries. #line:04ad8a3 
    <<jump nicola_explain_techniques>>
<<endif>>
===

title: nicola_explain_techniques
position: 450,300
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
<<card cava_romana>>
First technique\:he wooden wedge. #line:0a9cd74
<<card cuneo_legno>>
The Romans pushed fig-wood wedges into cracks in the rock. #line:03c8513
Then they soaked the wood — as it swelled, it split the stone! #line:06bf733 
Clever, wasn't it? #line:03ebc01 
<<jump nicola_technique_2>>
===

title: nicola_technique_2
position: 450,400
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Second technique\:explosives. #line:0317894
<<card esplosivi_1600>>
<<card esplosivi_cave>>
From 1600 onwards, workers used gunpowder in the quarries. #line:01e6420 
They blasted the mountainside to break off the blocks. #line:08716ce 
It was fast, but it destroyed a lot of marble. #line:01660f7 
And the damage to the environment was enormous. #line:0651468 
<<jump nicola_technique_3>>
===

title: nicola_technique_3
position: 450,500
group: nicola
color: blue
actor: SENIOR_M
---
Third technique\:the diamond wire. #line:0b0e7e9
<<card filo_diamantato>>
<<card macchinari_moderni>>
Since 1970, a steel wire coated in industrial diamonds has been used. #line:0c86963 
It cuts the rock with perfect precision and no waste. #line:09dc937 
In one day, you can cut what once took three whole months! #line:0868d02 
