title: bernini_explain_apollo
position: 450,900
group: bernini
color: blue
actor: ADULT_M
---
This sculpture captures the exact moment Daphne transforms into a laurel tree. #line:0883b38 
Her fingers become branches, her feet roots, her skin bark. #line:0c88e23 
All of this in marble — a rock as hard as iron! #line:078a707 
No one before me had dared to attempt such a thing. #line:0dc1400 
People believed marble could never look soft. #line:0120ed2 
I proved them wrong. #line:0f87afc 
<<jump bernini_explain_wire>>
===

title: bernini_explain_wire
position: 450,1000
group: bernini
color: blue
actor: ADULT_M
---
<<card macchinari_moderni>>
In my time, marble was cut with chisels and mallets. #line:0bd6466
Every millimetre was sweat and effort. #line:04b1303
Today there is the diamond wire: a steel wire coated in industrial diamonds. #line:0333357
<<card filo_diamantato>>
It runs at hundreds of metres per minute. #line:001f02c 
It slices through marble like butter, with no waste at all. #line:09940bf 
In a single day you can do the work that in my time took three months. #line:0eebc6b 
I wish I had had such a tool! #line:0baaa9b 
But enough talking — put my sculpture back together! #line:00e8fb9 
<<jump bernini_activity_intro>>
===

